[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Java class file generation**\n\nI'm thinking about whether generating a class file with `javac` actually counts as compiling. Maybe it’s safer to avoid that approach. Instead, I could consider writing a base64 decoded precomputed file, but that might mean I have to produce the bytes manually. Another option could be to use a library's `ClassFileWriter` in a small Java setup, which might work without needing to compile. I wonder if I can add test resource generation in Gradle without making things overly complicated.\n\n**Evaluating bytecode resources**\n\nI’m looking into how Bytecode interacts with `SecureCaller.class.getResource(\"SecureCallerImpl.clazz\")`. It seems it uses the defining classloader of SecureCaller instead of the thread context, which means I can’t use a custom context. The class’s loader is the application classloader, and I can add the resource effectively. I see that defining the resource file under `src/test/resources/net/sourceforge/htmlunit/corejs/javascript/SecureCallerImpl.clazz` might work. I’m considering copying from the original Rhino package or maybe searching the apt cache for this.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_046f90984e8f8a990169fa93be090c819f85a4e57c1313871c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-pPJx_AoRU_506Ir2ChLt9RfmrtFlANi0GJoSJlWdUK8wGq-VQM7u5QzMVWoA2fRNNDlaSMeE9ggzzXG5BM1gs6uqlEHorr5Q4rU3J0f5XsNyHK8b6gULOfjf8CQhhJ6ru_O3fKS3lY1jnXRl1EL43B9GlqLR485f6UsQMdcF9hUqNBy_AAR0Zt-8HY5IxAd0jI--1n5oqkS9wmBi2dH-4zThKBKCANvgFEL7-LulcYbG7vl1qDoTCxtoNci0SPLcuB-7Iq61Bz1vzFZsi0moCuUR76QAkoOi4AtrlocbdfATx6sXx2gYkYGrQxVyJM3_V1VNwR9WTplxRxpaDXgyDhDiM9MPOona7_kpEh0xlRWupKjwGkGO9VQ2GzyquIHhe7nlSFUahzt__AAVODDP1zl_kgxuxAsuzxylJ9LRuidIE4sFVKa9BfeAnlvd0Qf8BkjiX5Vae0abCzxrLFx-OdK5IL2RpbXy7oLkeb5_Etg5EU_5QdYrr98R1tJqcdST-FwOmjfbC8IZJzBH0eznlGZQ_zuQJu5TRsueAaGtGEjIIaxAjK-ue76uiHuoNZci7a05RJXNd-Xr6vIkejuGkBRJ